com.bluegosling.apt.testing

Interface CompilationContext.TaskBuilderWithProcessor

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CompilationContext.TaskBuilder
    Enclosing class:
    CompilationContext

    public static interface CompilationContext.TaskBuilderWithProcessor
extends CompilationContext.TaskBuilder
    Builds a task to run in this compilation context. For tasks with a processor under test, this interface provides an additional convenience method that simply invokes the processor under test.

    Other methods are overridden only to constrain the return type (covariance) for method chaining. If CompilationContext.TaskBuilder.run(CheckedProcessingTask) is invoked, the specified task will be executed and the TestEnvironment will indicate the processor under test with which the task can interact.

      • processingClasses

        CompilationContext.TaskBuilderWithProcessor processingClasses(Iterable<Class<?>> classes)
        Description copied from interface: CompilationContext.TaskBuilder
        Adds classes to be processed by the annotation processing round of compilation. Note that the classes and their annotations will be available for processing but will not be included in the first round's "root elements" since that indicates source elements to be processed. So you probably instead want CompilationContext.TaskBuilder.processingFiles(Iterable).
